org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.values

Class NumberValueMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.Message
      • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.BaseMessage
        • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.values.ValueMessage
          • org.team5940.pantry.logging.messages.values.NumberValueMessage

  • public class NumberValueMessage
extends ValueMessage
    A NumberValueMessage is a ValueMessage that can only take in numbers. The number is also optionally accompanied by a unit in the metadata.

    The units if being told in relation to another should be x*y^-p with x being the unit of measure, y being the unit being related to, and p being the degree of y. If it is "first unit per second unit to x power" then the degree has to be negative x.

    E.g: m*s^-2
    This notation would be meters per second squared.

    • Method Detail

      • createUnit

        public static java.lang.String createUnit(java.lang.String unit1,
                                          java.lang.String unit2,
                                          int power)
        Creates a unit with two given units with one in relation to the other.
        If the first unit is divided by the second one, the power is negative.
        If the power given is 0 then the method returns the unit1.
        If the power give is 1 then the method returns the unit1*unit2.
        If the power given is more than 1 then the method returns unit1*unit2^power
        Parameters:
        unit1 - The first unit in the unit relation.
        unit2 - The second unit in the unit relation that is multiplied with the first.
        power - The power of the second unit.
        Returns:
        The unit made from the inputs.
